claim: Flublok is produced using a novel production platform in which recombinant HA is expressed in insect cells using a baculovirus expression vector system (BEVS).
explanation: Multi-panel figure showing ELISA antibody titers. Panel A: log2 ELISA titers for egg-derived and cell-derived HA from influenza A(H3N2), A(H1N1)pdm09, B/Victoria, and B/Yamagata strains at Day 0 and 1 month post-vaccination. Panel B: geometric mean ratios of egg versus cell HA ELISA titers for H3, H1, B/VIC, and B/YAM. Panel C: log2 ELISA titers against H3 and H1 HA stalk antigens at Day 0 and 1 month. Panel D: geometric mean fold-rise of HA stalk ELISA titers (1 month/Day 0) for H3 and H1 stalks. The figure presents immunogenicity data (antibody titers) comparing egg- and cell-derived HA and stalk responses but does not mention Flublok, recombinant HA production, insect cells, or baculovirus expression vector system. Therefore, it does not support the claim. Note: Image quality is sufficient to read graphs and legends; no production method information is present.
